SIMPLE: noddle
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Noddle
<hw>Nod"dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>nodil</ets>,
<ets>nodle</ets>; perh. fr. <ets>nod</ets>, because the head is the
nodding part of the body, or perh. akin to E. <ets>knot</ets>; cf. Prov.
E. <ets>nod</ets> the nape of the neck.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
head; also, <altname>noodle</altname>; -- used jocosely or
contemptuously.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> noggin.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>Come, master, I have a project in my <qex>noddle</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The back part of the head or neck.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For occasion . . . turneth a bald <qex>noddle</qex>, after she
hath presented her locks in front, and no hold taken.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Noddy</ent>⟦br⟧
